  "texts": [
    "All embeddings are computed using a pretrained Sentence-BERT model [54] (sentence-transformers/stsb-roberta-base-v2 on Huggingfacefoot_7), which captures sentence-level semantics appropriate for lengthy reviews and outputs.",
    "A positive value of the relative cosine similarity means higher expression of the positive steering trait, and vice versa for the negative steering trait.",
    "Similarity scores, rather than hard classification, allows the evaluation to capture more nuanced intensities of preference expressions.Furthermore, as the magnitude of steering increases, we expect to see a degeneracy in the quality of the LLM's outputs.",
    "To evaluate this, we compute the perplexity-normalized effect (PNE), which incorporates a measure of how the model's perplexity, a proxy for degeneration, changes with steering compared to a nonsteered baseline.",
    "This equation is given by von Rütte et al."
  ],
